# Security Patterns

## Input Validation

- **Backend**: Validate all inputs at API boundaries (Pydantic/Zod)
- **Frontend**: Validate user inputs before sending to API
- **Sanitization**: Sanitize user inputs before LLM prompts (prevent prompt injection)
- **Rate limiting**: Rate limit API endpoints

## Authentication & Authorization

- **Backend**: Authenticate all API requests (JWT, OAuth, API keys)
- **Frontend**: Store tokens securely (httpOnly cookies preferred)
- **Least privilege**: Use least privilege principle
- **Audit logs**: Audit access logs

## Data Protection

- **Encryption**: Encrypt sensitive data at rest
- **TLS/HTTPS**: Use TLS/HTTPS for data in transit
- **PII masking**: Mask PII in logs
- **Secrets**: Never store secrets in frontend code

## Frontend Security

- **XSS prevention**: Sanitize user-generated content
- **CSRF protection**: Use CSRF tokens for state-changing operations
- **CSP**: Implement Content Security Policy headers
- **API keys**: Never expose API keys in frontend code (use backend proxy)

## Dependency Security

- **Vulnerability scanning**: Scan for known vulnerabilities (npm audit, pip-audit, Snyk)
- **Dependency updates**: Regularly update dependencies
- **Automated scanning**: Integrate security scanning in CI/CD
- **Security advisories**: Review security advisories
